Scripts to start a mamba appliction on system boot
Robert Oliveira <olivecoder@gmail.com>


HOW TO ADD TO YOUR PROJECT
git clone git://development/u/robert/mamba-init init && rm -rf init/.git


HOW TO INSTALL THE INIT SCRIPT
sudo init/install.sh


HOW TO CHANGE THE MAMBA APPLICATION USER TO RUN AS
sudo vi /etc/defaults/<mamba-application-name>


HOW TO SET TO START ON BOOT
sudo chkconfig <mamba-application-name> on


HOW TO START/STOP/RESTART AS NORMAL USER
/etc/init.d/<mamba-application-name> start
/etc/init.d/<mamba-application-name> stop
/etc/init.d/<mamba-application-name> restart


HOW TO START/STOP/RESTART AS ROOT 
sudo service <mamba-application-name> start
sudo service <mamba-application-name> stop
sudo service <mamba-application-name> restart
-- or --
sudo /etc/init.d/<mamba-application-name> start
sudo /etc/init.d/<mamba-application-name> stop
sudo /etc/init.d/<mamba-application-name> restart
